We want $\mathbf{b}$ to bisect the angle between $\mathbf{a}$ and $\mathbf{c},$ so we want
\[\frac{\mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{b}}{\|\mathbf{a}\| \|\mathbf{b}\|} = \frac{\mathbf{b} \cdot \mathbf{c}}{\|\mathbf{b}\| \|\mathbf{c}\|}.\]Then
\[\frac{\begin{pmatrix} 7 \\ -4 \\ -4 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} x \\ y \\ z \end{pmatrix}}{\left\| \begin{pmatrix} 7 \\ -4 \\ -4 \end{pmatrix} \right\| \left\| \begin{pmatrix} x \\ y \\ z \end{pmatrix} \right\|} = \frac{\begin{pmatrix} x \\ y \\ z \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} -2 \\ -1 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix}}{\left\| \begin{pmatrix} x \\ y \\ z \end{pmatrix} \right\| \left\| \begin{pmatrix} -2 \\ -1 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix} \right\|}.\]Hence,
\[\frac{7x - 4y - 4z}{\sqrt{81}} = \frac{-2x - y + 2z}{3}.\]Then $21(7x - 4y - 4z) = -9(2x + y - 2z),$ or $147x + 76y - 62z = 0.$  Taking $y = 1$ and $z = 0,$ we find $x = \frac{31}{147}.$  Therefore, $\mathbf{b} = \boxed{\begin{pmatrix} \frac{31}{147} \\ 1 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}}.$

